===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# One of a set of items which do not need to be specified; often used in conjunction with the catch phrase [[yadda yadda yadda]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|2001|November 8|Jim Mateja|Kia opens door, manually, to minivan market|Chicago Tribune|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-7378060_ITM
|passage=Sedona offers everything a Caravan, Voyager, T&C, yadda, yadda, yadda does, {{...}} However, when V-6-equipped, the '''yaddas''' are a lot more quiet leaving the light or pulling into the passing lane.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|2004|August 28|Gary Peterson|Tina Thompson: `I really wanted to be part of this. This is my time'|Contra Costa Times|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-8540064_ITM
|passage=Dropouts include Jason Kidd (recovering from knee surgery), Ray Allen (getting married this summer), Tracy McGrady (security concerns), Karl Malone (recovering from the NBA season; lost his mother), Jermaine O'Neal (banged up), Vince Carter ('''yadda'''), Mike Bibby ('''yadda'''), Elton Brand ('''yadda'''), and Kenyon Martin ('''yadda''').}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|2006|May 13||A Tough Road: Bennerman, Who Went To Hargrave, Describes Exactly What Glenn's Wallace Is Going To Be Experiencing|Winston-Salem Journal|url=http://moreresults.factiva.com/results/index/index.aspx?ref=XWSJ000020060514e25d0000q
|passage=So right or wrong, good move or bad, '''yadda''' or '''yadda''', it's an intriguing development in this gifted player's life and basketball career.}}
